# 3. 彩りに隠された本音

Mizuki: Whoa! This is awesome! We're not even at the top and you can see all those mountains way over there!
Ena: Yeah, it's so beautiful...!
Ena: Oh, wait. I should take some pictures too. They could come in handy when I draw later.
Mizuki: What's this? Ena's not immediately going for some selfies? Interesting...!
Ena: *Sigh*... It's not like that's the only thing I ever think about, you know?
Airi: Hey, I'm getting pretty hungry. Why don't we have lunch here and enjoy the view? I made enough food for all of us.
Mizuki: Oh, me too! I'm starving!
Shizuku: Hehe. Everything Airi makes is so good too. I'm excited to see what she brought today.
Ena: Wow...! This looks amazing!
Airi: I made most of it last night and tried to include something that everyone likes.
Mizuki: Yeah, it looks delicious! Let's dig in♪ Oh, perfect! French fries!
Airi: Ena told me that you like them a lot, Mizuki. I made them a little well-done to keep them from getting too soggy!
Shizuku: Wait, but this one tastes like...
Airi: Fried tofu skins. You requested them, Shizuku, so I decided to make some. I wrapped them around some pieces of chicken.
Shizuku: *Nom*... Oh, it's delicious...! You're such a good cook, Airi!
Airi: And I made some cheesecake for you, Ena. This one has a lemony zest to it.
Ena: Yay! I still can't help but think your cheesecake is store bought, you know?
Mizuki: Mmm! Everything's so good!
Mizuki: You're awesome, Airi! You go to school while being an idol and you make amazing food?!
Airi: Oh, this is nothing. As for being an idol, we support each member as a team, and everyone's been a huge help so far.
Mizuki: Yeah, I get that. Also, what was your group called again? MORE MORE JUMP!?
Airi: Yup. We mainly make videos and do livestreams.
Ena: Speaking of which, I saw one of your streams the other day. You guys were doing dance practice and stuff...
Shizuku: You did?! Thank you so much! But we had to try so many times to get it right. I doubt it was very interesting from your point of view...
Ena: Yeah, you kept messing up in the beginning, but it was also pretty heartwarming in the end...
Shizuku: Huh?
Ena: No matter how many times you failed, Shizuku, you kept trying and got it perfect in the end, right?
Ena: After I saw you do that, I felt like trying a little harder myself...
Shizuku: Ena, I don't know what to say... Thank you...
Airi: Good for you, Shizuku! I'm sure Ena's not alone either.
Shizuku: Right! Hehe. I feel like I've taken a step towards becoming an idol who delivers hope...
Mizuki: An idol who delivers hope, huh...?
Ena: Is something wrong?
Mizuki: No, I just thought that's pretty incredible is all. I wouldn't even know where to start if I decided to try giving someone hope...
Airi: But you two make songs together, right? Isn't that another way to do just that?
Mizuki: You think so? It'd be nice if that were true...
Ena: Mizuki...?
Shizuku: Is something the matter, Mizuki?
Mizuki: Uh, no! It's nothing! Anyways, Airi, can I have some more of those french fries?
Airi: Yeah, go for it. I'm glad you like them so much.
Mizuki: Yay! Thanks!
Ena: (Was Mizuki about to just...?)
Ena: ...
Mizuki: Thanks for the food!
Mizuki: That was so good, Airi! I'm stuffed!
Airi: You're very welcome. You guys didn't leave even a single crumb, so it was worth the effort.
Airi: Now, we should probably get going soon...
Shizuku: Hm? There's quite a few people gathered over there. I wonder what's going on?
Staff: Register here for the Green Adventure! Please make sure to fill out the necessary forms if you wish to participate!
Shizuku: The Green Adventure?
Airi: Oh, it's the game where you guess the names of plants and rivers while you're hiking.
Ena: Huh? How did you know that?
Airi: One of the guides that I saw after we got off the bus told me. Anyone can join as long as they register for it. Wanna give it a try?
Mizuki: Oh, me! Let's go!
Ena: Are you sure? There could be a bunch of bugs over that way, you know...?
Shizuku: Then how about Mizuki and Airi go join them, while Ena and I have a look around here...?
Airi: Sounds like a plan!
Ena: Wait, but Mizuki's...
Shizuku: Airi may just be able to get something out of Mizuki. How about we leave her to it just for now?
Ena: Shizuku...
Airi: Alright, we're gonna go for a perfect score! Ready, Mizuki?!
Mizuki: Yeah! Let's hurry and get registered, Airi!
Nene: Whoa...!
Nene: It's so green and beautiful...! Almost like an open-world RPG!
Rui: That sounds like exactly something you'd say, Nene.
Rui: Anyways, that should be enough stretching for now. How about we start with a little jog?
Rui: There's even a trail running course over there too. Let's go take a look.
Nene: Huh? This is all we're doing? It seems too normal, you know...?
Rui: Oh, you'll need to wear this while you run...
Nene: What is this, chainmail?! It's so heavy...!
Rui: It's a weighted jacket, but I also added quite a few features to make sure it's safe to use. Unfortunately, it ended up weighing more than I expected.
Rui: You'll also need to put on these knee braces, as well as this helmet. It should fit right over your cap...
Nene: Wait, what?! All of these...?!
Rui: Ah, perfect!
Nene: I-It feels so clunky... You turned me into a robot, Rui...
Rui: Now, let's start running! Try your best, Nene! I'll be right there with you!
Nene: Hnng...! It's... So... Heavy...!
